{{About||senior version|Turkvision Song Contest 2017}} {{Infobox song contest | name = Bala Turkvision Song Contest | year = 2017 | theme = Bala Türkvizyon 2017 | logo = | semi = | final = cancelled | presenters = | exsupervisor = | exproducer = | director = | winner = | vote = A juror from each region evaluates all the songs on a 10 point system. | host = [[Adam Media Group]] | venue = [[Saryarka Velodrome]], [[Astana]], [[Kazakhstan]] | entries = 5 (to date) | debut = | return = | withdraw = | interval = | opening = <!-- Map Legend Colours --> | Green = | Green SA = Y | Purple = Y | Red = | Yellow = }}
'''Bala Turkvision Song Contest 2017''' ({{lang-tr|Bala Türkvizyon Şarkı Yarışması 2017}}) was to be the second edition of the [[Bala Turkvision Song Contest]], which was to take place at the [[Saryarka Velodrome]], in Astana, Kazakhstan; and organised by [[Adam Media Group]]. The contest was originally scheduled to take place in December 2016, but was cancelled due to on-going events in Turkey. Only five [[List of Turkic dynasties and countries|Turkic regions]], which have either a large Turkic population or a widely spoken Turkic language, confirmed their participation in the contest before it was cancelled for the second year running on October 20, 2017. As of now, the future of the Bala Turkvision Song Contest remains uncertain.
==Location== [[File:Saryarka Velodrome.JPG|thumb|[[Saryarka Velodrome]], venue for the 2017 edition.|150px|left]] The contest was originally scheduled to take place in Turkey, but was later announced as being cancelled due to the [[December 2016 Istanbul bombings]], marking the first time since the inaugural contest in 2015 that a cancellation of the contest had occurred.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Turkvision Song Contest delayed until March|url=https://eurovoix-world.com/turkvision-song-contest-delayed-march/|website=eurovoix-world.com|publisher=Eurovoix|date=8 December 2016|accessdate=1 March 2017}}</ref>
In February 2017 it was announced by Ministry of Culture and Sports in Kazakhstan, that the 2017 edition would take place in [[Astana]], [[Kazakhstan]], and would coincide with other events taking place in the city as part of [[Expo 2017]].<ref name="TSC2017">{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Turkvision Song Contest 2017 to be held in Kazakhstan|url=https://eurovoix-world.com/turkvision-song-contest-2017-to-be-held-in-kazakhstan/|website=eurovoix-world.com|publisher=Eurovoix|date=15 February 2017|accessdate=1 March 2017}}</ref>
The contest was originally going to be held at the [[Barys Arena]], in [[Astana]], [[Kazakhstan]].<ref name="Barys Arena">{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Turkvision 17 Barys Arena announced as venue|url=https://eurovoix-world.com/turkvision17-barys-arena-announced-venue/|website=eurovoix-world.com|publisher=Eurovoix|date=16 February 2017|accessdate=1 March 2017}}</ref>
